<TEXT>
the vatican said today that open dissent 
cannot be tolerated and ordered theologians to refrain from 
publicly challenging church teaching 
a major document issued by the congregation for the doctrine of 
the faith replied in strong terms to western theologians who have 
questioned the roman catholic church ban on artificial birth 
control papal authority and other issues 
to succumb to the temptation of dissent is to allow the 
leaven of infidelity to the holy spirit to start to work said 
the report approved by pope john paul ii 
the document defended punitive action taken against dissidents 
and said theologians must adhere to doctrine whether it is 
infallible or not it rejected the notion that the church should 
leave moral and sexual matters to personal choice or conscience 
it warned dissenters against making their complaints in the 
media or trying to influence public opinion 
last year 170 germanspeaking theology professors issued a 
widely publicized statement criticizing the pope for his opposition 
to contraception and his exercise of power 
west german cardinal josef ratzinger head of the congregation 
told a news conference that the vatican document was not a direct 
response to the german declaration but addressed the general 
climate of conflict fomented by dissident theologians 
during john pauls 11year papacy several theologians have been 
punished for straying from church positions on birth control and 
other issues of sexual morality they include the rev charles e 
curran who was stripped of his right to teach theology at catholic 
university in washington dc in 1987 
the 28page document called instruction on the ecclesial 
vocation of the theologian was written by ratzinger a strict 
doctrinal conservative and the popes guardian of orthodoxy 
in a blunt appraisal of the situation the document said 
theology is sometimes exposed to risks and moments of crisis and 
tension open dissent by theologians has caused serious harm 
to the church it said 
the document said theologians might in some cases question the 
timeliness the form or even the contents of some church 
teaching in such an event they should try to resolve the 
differences in dialogue with bishops it said 
however if in the end a theologian still can not accept the 
teaching he should keep quiet it said 
such a situation can certainly prove a difficult trial the 
document said it can be a call to suffer for the truth in 
silence and prayer but with the certainty that if the truth 
really is at stake it will ultimately prevail 
ratzingers report said the church cannot be run like a 
democracy a position voiced by the pope on several occasions 
standards of conduct appropriate to civil society or the 
workings of a democracy cannot be purely and simply applied to the 
church it said 
