<TEXT>
merchants shut stores and cleared shelves 
this week to make room for a deluge of western goods forcing east 
germans to forage for food and other necessities during the 
nations hectic last days as a socialist state 
officials disagreed over who was to blame for widespread 
shortages 
theres no soap here no meat said ines kroll a 
25yearold mother of two as she pushed her shopping cart past 
depleted shelves in the only store in blankenburg a small town 
north of berlin 
many stores selling household goods closed to clear space for 
the western products that will pour into the country after sunday 
when the germanys merge their economies 
some merchants said they also wanted to avoid taking in large 
amounts of east german marks in the days before the nearly 
worthless currency is replaced by the valuable west german mark 
experts say many east german companies are keeping their 
products off the market until next week when they can sell them 
for west german marks 
grocery stores have been canceling their orders with east german 
suppliers and letting their stocks run out 
next week well get the west products and the customers will 
have west german marks said liane fischer a clerk at the 
blankenburg store 
lines of up to 1000 people snaked down sidewalks as people 
converged on banks to fill out paperwork necessary for converting 
savings accounts to west german marks 
the government in an attempt to protect its ailing industries 
from the first rush of western competition announced tuesday a 
series of tariffs on western goods beginning sunday 
an 11 percent tariff is to be imposed through the end of the 
year replaced the following quarter by a 6 percent tariff 
food will not be affected east germanys huge farm collectives 
are expected to be battered by western agricultural producers 
however it is uncertain if the tariffs will remain if the 
current pace of unification continues and the nations are fully 
unified in december 
many stores are already stocking west german goods under 
agreements made in march that allowed a limited entry of some 
products into the country 
but many staples still were in short supply mrs kroll said she 
could find no detergent and rejected the skimpy selection of meat 
she also had mixed feelings about the end of the east german mark 
my husband mints east german coins for a living she said 
some experts say 1 million to 4 million workers will lose their 
jobs in the first two years of economic unification 
many of the heavy industries that were once the backbone of the 
former centrally planned economy are expected to fail as they face 
leaner more efficient western concerns 
the small businesses that will suddenly become independent are 
expected to have a much better chance of survival than the large 
inefficient factories that churn out outmoded cars electronics and 
other products 
dietmar mueller a spkesman for the east german economics 
ministry said retailers can make more money by selling west german 
goods which have profit margins sometimes three times as high as 
east german goods 
merchants have not ordered enough from east german producers 
because merchants think people wont buy them he said the 
result he said is that consumers have to bite the bullet and 
buy the much more expensive west german goods 
but werner schwartz spokesman for the commerce ministry which 
represents small businesses said east german goods have merely 
sold out 
the government last month ordered massive price cuts to clear 
textiles electronics and other goods that customers were refusing 
to buy some televisions for example were cut by 90 percent 
cord schwartau an expert on east german industry for the german 
institute for economic research in west berlin said both officials 
are correct 
he said the amazingly low prices of unattractive goods 
helped move them off shelves but that merchants also have been 
refusing to order new east german goods because they fear consumers 
wont want them 
he said many east german manufacturers themselves are keeping 
their goods off the market so they can take advantage of higher 
prices that are expected after sunday 
</TEXT>
