experts say some of the drugs sent to soviet 
armenia for victims of the 1988 earthquake were useless or even 
dangerous and they say there could be similar problems with 
emergency supplies now being sent to iran 
supplies sent to armenia included pharmaceuticals that came from 
stocks of expired drugs and others of a type no longer sold 
according to an article in the lancet a respected british medical 
journal 
the quantities of expired and useless drugs are especially 
worrying the june 9 issue said the supply of massive amounts 
of drugs for the purpose of humanitarian aid still represents a 
good way of disposing of stocks of expired drugs or of those that 
are normally no longer marketable 
the article was wriiten dr philippe autier an epidemiologist 
