said it could take anywhere from 30 to 60 days to draw up the final 
documents on the financial package intended to shore up trumps 
empire 
a spokesman for trump dan klores refused to comment on the 
report of a deal but said he hoped to have a statement later in the 
day 
some 65 to 70 banks and their attorneys are involved in the 
process all but one bank agreed in principle to the deal 
the german bank dresdner bank ag continued to balk but attorneys 
decided that dresdners endorsement wasnt essential 
dresdner whose 15 million loan to trump is secured by the 
first lien on the trump tower fifth avenue residential and 
commercial skyscraper has been opposed to placing a second lien on 
the building 
it was decided last night that dresdners holdout wouldnt 
prevent the deal from going forward the source said 
trump faces a midnight deadline to cover principal and interest 
payments due on bonds sold to finance the trump castle hotel and 
casino in atlantic city nj the process of making those payments 
began today after seven key banks extended the 20 million bridge 
loan to trump 
trump had missed a june 15 deadline for the casino bond payment 
but a 10day grace period extended the time to tonight a 
declaration of default could allow creditors to seize various trump 
properties used as collateral to back the bonds and other loans 
and could affect his licenses to run casinos in atlantic city 
trump also is overdue on a 30 million bank loan payment to a 
group led by manufacturers hanover trust 
