a federal judge says the rev donald wildmon 
must stop using a pamphlet to support his groups antipornography 
campaign because it misrepresents the artists work and may harm 
the artists reputation 
the judge however said wildmons tupelo missbased american 
family association could use the pamphlets if it makes it clear the 
pictures being used were only fragments and not the artists entire 
work 
the case was brought to us district court in manhattan after 
east village artist david wojnarowicz learned the organization was 
distributing pamphlets with pieces of his work taken from much 
larger collages 
one picture taken from a multilayered work shows christ with a 
hypodermic needle in his arm 
wildmons group mailed out about 6000 pamphlets to members of 
congress clergy and media outlets to bolster its view that the 
national endowment for the arts supports pornography 
the nea gave the illinois state university galleries a 15000 
grant which they used to hold a wojnarowicz retrospective last 
winter and publish a catalogue containing his work 
after viewing wojnarowiczs work wildmon said i kind of got 
sick to my stomach he testified at a oneday trial that he was 
angry and upset because tax dollars went to help pay for some of 
this 
wojnarowicz claimed the pamphlet was a gross distortion of his 
work and filed a 1 million damage lawsuit charging the pamphlet 
violated copyright laws 
judge william c conner on monday agreed in part with 
wojnarowicz and issued a temporary injunction saying the afa could 
not use the pamphlet as it was 
the pamphlet could be construed by reasonable persons as 
misrepresenting the work of the artist with bringing harm to the 
artists reputation and to the value of his works the judge said 
wildmons attorney benjamin w bull objected to the ruling he 
said the pamphlet was protected by the first amendments freedom of 
speech 
the judge said the pamphlet could be used if it contained a 
clarifying statement 
conner said he would rule next month on the monetary and 
copyright infringement complaints 
wildmon and his group have for years led the conservative 
campaigns against films music television shows magazines and art 
that they deem obscene 
i consider this to be a vindication of sorts the artist 
said after the judge issued mondays ruling 
i didnt know mr wojnarowicz personally and had no knowledge 
