the bush administration today announced 
partial plans for protecting the rare northern spotted owl at the 
cost of at least 1000 logging jobs in the northwest 
but for the second time in less than a week officials delayed 
issuing a complete blueprint designed to save the bird without 
devastating the regions timber industry 
