administration before pressing for a vote 
a key stumbling block to an agreement had been the bush 
administrations proposals for increasing down payment requirements 
as part of a package of reforms aimed at halting massive losses 
that threaten the federal housing administration program 
the bush administration proposed increasing premiums and upfront 
cash requirements so that fha borrowers would have to pay 
twothirds of closing costs at the time of purchase sen alfonse 
damato rny proposed going further by requiring a 5 percent 
down payment on loans over 5000 adding a premium over the life 
of the loan and requiring that all closing costs be paid at the 
beginning of the loan without being financed 
