air conditioners whined swimming pools beckoned 
but there was no getting around it it was hot here tuesday 122 
degrees worth of hot hot enough to ground planes it was the 
hottest day on record in americas hottest big city 
a heat wave that stretched from the southern california coast to 
the heart of texas reached its sweltering peak in phoenix which 
set an alltime record of 120 degrees on monday and promptly broke 
it a day later 
at 247 pm it was 122 and many of the airlines at sky harbor 
international airport began canceling takeoffs said airport 
spokesman rick martinez 
the national weather service advised the metropolitan areas 21 
million residents to stay indoors carry plenty of water when 
driving and not leave pets or children inside parked cars 
six firefighters died and five others including four men from 
a prison workcrew were seriously burned fighting a 1900acre 
fire in tonto national forest about 90 miles northeast of phoenix 
forest spokeswoman joyce hassell said 
the temperature tuesday topped 106 in payson 12 miles southwest 
of the fire area it wasnt known immediately what role the heat 
might have played in the tragedy 
spot checks at sky harbor indicated most airlines were resuming 
flights later tuesday afternoon as temperatures dropped below 120 
american airlines canceled all its afternoon flights in an out of 
phoenix officials at the companys offices here said 
it was the first time planes had been grounded because of heat 
in the history of sky harbor the worlds 20th busiest airport 
martinez said 
the heat had reduced lift to the point that planes had no margin 
for error trying to get airborne he said some landings also were 
rerouted to other airlines martinez said 
temperature is really critical on takeoff martinez said 
people are staying in the gates waiting for the temperature to 
go down 
it is what we consider a severe weather condition not unlike 
your northern california fog conditions or similar weather 
conditions said america west airlines spokesman dick shimizu 
