jones of castledale utah drove into town with his wife suzanne 
in an airconditioned car when they stepped out he said it 
took our breath away 
mondays high of 120 broke the old record of 118 degrees that 
had been set on four occasions the last time on july 4 1989 
tuesday mornings low of 91 degrees also set a record for the 
date and was close to the 93degree reading of july 20 1989 which 
was the highest low temperature ever recorded here 
