<TEXT>
when henry mancini was a kid in the steel town 
of aliquippa pa the fourth of july wasnt that big a deal he 
recalls no big parades no rockets red glare no sousa marches 
however he notesi grew up in an almost 100 percent italian 
neighborhood where patriotism was alive and well but the big 
events were the august festas parties celebrating the feast of 
st anthony and the like 
next wednesday though hell be part of a big july 4 deal on 
pbs a 90minute musical celebration a capitol fourth 1990 
hosted by beverly sills and broadcast live from washington itll 
