<TEXT>
 
a jenny lind recital northeastern elizabeth parcells 
soprano james winn piano robert honeysucker baritone 
 
in 1850 jenny lind the worldrenowned swedish nightingale 
conquered the united states in particularly hysterical fashion 
befitting her promoter pt barnum his centurys combination of 
our donalds king trump and kirschner linds triumphal tour plays 
no small part in the nations music history 
northeastern an admirable small recording company based in 
saxonville mass devoted to american music has tried to bring 
lind back to life parcells reproduces on disc a typical concert 
that lind might have given during the tour 
she sings with complete security a clean sound excellent 
diction and tight vibrato but there is a certain inflexibility in 
her phrasing particularly in mozarts queen of the night aria from 
the magic flute that lind probably didnt have by all 
contemporary accounts technically though parcells is impeccable 
and she does evoke what one imagines to be the nordic purity and 
songbird brilliance of her predecessor 
the program the notes tell us is typically lind on the 
opening oratorio number on mighty pens from haydns 
creation here operatic showpieces such as ma la sola 
ohime son io from bellinis beatrice di tenda a comic duet 
with baritone from rossinis il turco in italia a piano 
interlude and popular songs 
lind often ended her programs with home sweet home and 
parcells offers a lovely version sung with appealing simplicity 
the real praise should go to northeastern for producing such an 
imaginative disc and so many other highly worthwhile projects in 
recent years 
by daniel wakin associated press writer 
</TEXT>
