national through a 312 million convertible preferred stock 
transaction 
the two companies also will enter into a series of business 
relationships to offer investment management services reinsurance 
pension products and group health products lincoln national said 
in a news release 
this is a very attractive arrangement for both lincoln 
national and daiichi mutual life said ian m rolland president 
and chief executive officer of lincoln national it offers 
strategic opportunities for both of our companies 
daiichi mutual life is the worlds third largest insurance 
company it reported assets of 110 billion and revenue of 23 
billion in its fiscal year ended march 31 
lincoln national reported assets of 251 billion and revenue 
exceeding 81 billion in the year ended dec 31 
the companies will exchange trainees to improve understanding of 
their respective markets rolland said 
we are hopeful this will give lincoln national greater 
visibility in the international equity markets and provide better 
business opportunities particularly in japan he said 
the agreement which must be approved by federal regulators 
calls for daiichi to purchase a 5 percent share of lincoln 
national through the first series of convertible preferred stock 
and a 46 percent share through a second series within a year 
we think lincoln national is a highly regarded and soundly 
managed company said takahide sakurai president of daiichi 
mutual life insurance co in a statement from tokyo this 
transaction offers us a good investment opportunity 
lincoln national and daiichi entered into a reinsurance 
agreement in 1987 the two companies relationship dates to visits 
by daiichi officials to fort wayne almost 30 years ago rolland 
said 
this is an alliance for two companies who are familiar with 
each others strengths and values he said we both believe 
that good customer service is vital we both believe that sound 
investment practices are the key to our businesses 
and we both believe that future growth and prosperity relies 
upon our finding new opportunities in our industry 
