publishing and communications concern said tuesday it had a profit 
of 1011 million pounds or about 175 million at current exchange 
rates in its latest fiscal year 
robert maxwell chairman and chief executive said the results 
were highly satisfactory for a year which saw the company 
complete its move out of printing and into international publishing 
he said the company hopes to raise 950 million from further 
asset sales to reduce debt but declined to identify what 
properties are for sale 
in reporting its results for the year ended march 31 the 
company provided for comparison results from a 15month period 
ended march 31 1989 when it said it earned 190 million pounds the 
company has changed to operating on a fiscal year rather than 
calendar year basis 
