on the other hand fitzwater said i dont think that it 
bushs statement is that big a change were still a long way 
from the final details of a settlement 
there is a general consensus among budget negotiators that they 
need to reduce the deficit by 45 billion to 60 billion in the 
fiscal year beginning oct 1 and about 400 billion to 600 billion 
over the next five years 
technically the grammrudman deficit reduction law would 
require far deeper cuts based on current revenue and spending 
projections by law the government will be forced to absorb deep 
acrosstheboard spending cuts unless the deficit is kept to 74 
billion in fiscal 1991 
